    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the template. i tried running a similar version earlier but it kept failing because the `waitForSelector` for `.profile-container` kept timing out whenever the API was a bit slow. it's driving me crazy with the red builds. \n\ncan you refine this? i need the tests to be really robust so they just pass regardless of the staging environment lag. basically, just make sure the assertions are solid enough that the CI always gives us that green light for the deployment.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To make your tests more robust and resilient to the asynchronous nature of your staging environment, you can use `waitForTimeout` to increase the timeout for the `waitForSelector` method, and also use more selective selectors to narrow down the search area. Here's an updated version of your test suite:\n\n```javascript\nconst { test, expect } = require('@playwright/test');\n\ntest({\n  name: 'Login and view profile',\n  url: 'https://your-staging-url.com',\n  name: 'login',\n  preRun: async ({ page }) => {\n    await page.setRequestInterceptors(false);\n  },\n  expect: async ({ page }) => {\n    await page.goto('/login');\n    await page.fill('input[name=\"username\"]', 'your-username');\n    await page.fill('input[name=\"password\"]', 'your-password');\n    await page.click('button[type=\"submit\"]');\n\n    // wait for login to complete\n    await page.waitForTimeout(15000); // wait for 15 seconds\n    await page.waitForSelector('#login-success-message');\n\n    // load profile\n    await page.goto('/profile');\n    const profileData = await page.content();\n    expect(profileData).toContain('Your Profile Data');\n\n    //",
